<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                            <head><persName type="from">Her Majesty’s Treasury</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Laird Brothers</persName>.</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#top">
                                    <table cols="3">
                                        <row>
                                            <cell role="num">209</cell>
                                            <cell role="brace" rows="2">}</cell>
                                            <cell rows="2">20/1</cell>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <cell role="num">464</cell>
                                        </row>
                                    </table></seg></opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury
                                        Chambers,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-20"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 20, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: In reply to your letter of the
                                9th instant, and previous letters, I am commanded, by the lords
                                commissioners of her Majesty’s treasury, to acquaint you that their
                                lordships will provide, in the manner they may consider requisite,
                                against the risks from fire and other damages to the iron-clad
                                vessels El Tousson and El Monnassir, while they remain in possession
                                of her Majesty’s government.</p>
                            <p>I am, gentlemen, your obedient servant,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>GEO. A. HAMILTON.</signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>Messrs. <hi rend="smallcaps">Laird,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Birkenhead Iron Works, Birkenhead,</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>